'''Dennis Hadžikadunić''' ({{IPA|bs|dêːnis xǎdʒikadunitɕ|pron}}; born 9 July 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Serie B]] club [[UC Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], on loan from [[FC Rostov|Rostov]]. Born in Sweden, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Hadžikadunić started his professional career at [[Malmö FF]], who sent him on loan to [[Trelleborgs FF]] in 2018. Later that year, he joined Rostov, who loaned him back to Malmö FF in 2022, to [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] in 2023, to [[Hamburger SV]] later that year and to Sampdoria in 2025.

A former Swedish youth international, Hadžikadunić made his senior international debut for Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2020, earning over 30 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Malmö FF===
Hadžikadunić started playing football at a local club [[BK Olympic]], before joining the youth academy of his hometown team [[Malmö FF]] in 2012. In September 2016, he signed his first professional contract with the squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/da-li-je-ovo-nasljednik-emira-spahica|title=Da li je ovo nasljednik Emira Spahića?|website=sportske.ba|date=18 November 2019|access-date=18 November 2019|language=bs}}</ref> On 26 October, he made his professional debut against [[Gefle IF|Gefle]] at the age of 18.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/malmo-u-pretposljednjem-kolu-porazen-od-geflea/234406|title=Malmö u pretposljednjem kolu poražen od Geflea|website=sportsport.ba|date=26 October 2016|access-date=28 October 2016|language=bs}}</ref> He won his first trophy with the club on 16 October 2017, when they were crowned league champions.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/malmo-je-prvak-svedske-golcina-za-kraj-i-ludilo-na-terenu/255460|title=Malmö je prvak Švedske: Golčina za kraj i ludilo na terenu|website=sportsport.ba|date=17 October 2017|access-date=17 October 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2018, he was loaned to [[Trelleborgs FF]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/said-hadzikadunic-ponosan-sam-na-dennisovu-odluku-da-igra-za-bih-komunikacija-sa-savezom-je-bila-dobra|title=Said Hadžikadunić: Ponosan sam na Dennisovu odluku da igra za BiH, komunikacija sa savezom je bila dobra|website=scsport.ba|date=21 August 2020|access-date=23 August 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

===Rostov===
In July, Hadžikadunić was transferred to Russian side [[FC Rostov|Rostov]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/bosanac-potpisao-za-ruskog-premijerligasa|title=Bosanac potpisao za ruskog premijerligaša|website=sportske.ba|date=14 July 2018|access-date=17 July 2018|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the squad against [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]] on 10 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/sunjic-se-vratio-u-sastav-dynamu-bod-u-rostovu/298490|title=Šunjić se vratio u sastav, Dynamu bod u Rostovu|website=sportsport.ba|date=10 November 2018|access-date=13 November 2018|language=bs}}</ref> On 8 July 2020, he scored his first professional goal against [[FC Ufa|Ufa]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/303982-mladi-hadzikadunic-zabio-je-gol-za-rostov-pred-plasmanom-su-u-europa-ligu|title=Mladi Hadžikadunić zabio je gol za Rostov, pred plasmanom su u Europa Ligu|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=9 July 2020|access-date=11 July 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In March 2022, he was loaned to his former club Malmö FF until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/dennis-hadzikadunic-napustio-rusiju-i-vratio-se-kuci/117885|title=Dennis Hadžikadunić napustio Rusiju i vratio se kući|website=faktor.ba|date=11 March 2022|access-date=13 March 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2023, he was sent on a six-month loan to Spanish outfit [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/802186/dennis-hadzikadunic-je-novi-igrac-mallorce|title=Dennis Hadžikadunić je novi igrač Mallorce|website=avaz.ba|date=18 January 2023|access-date=18 January 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In July, he was loaned to German side [[Hamburger SV]] for the remainder of the campaign. In July 2024, his loan was extended for an additional season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/dennis-hadzikadunic-ce-i-naredne-sezone-igrati-u-njemackoj|title=Dennis Hadžikadunić će i naredne sezone igrati u Njemačkoj|website=scsport.ba|date=1 July 2024|access-date=1 July 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In September 2025, he was sent on a season-long loan to Italian team [[UC Sampdoria|Sampdoria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/hadzikadunic-ima-novi-klub-preselio-u-italiju|title=Hadžikadunić ima novi klub, preselio u Italiju|website=n1info.ba|date=1 September 2025|access-date=1 September 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Despite representing [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] at all youth levels, Hadžikadunić decided to play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at the senior level.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/stoper-ruskog-rostova-dennis-hadzikadunic-igrat-ce-za-bosnu-i-hercegovinu/200811139|title=Štoper ruskog Rostova Dennis Hadžikadunić igrat će za Bosnu i Hercegovinu|website=klix.ba|date=11 August 2020|access-date=13 August 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In September 2020, his request to change sports citizenship from Swedish to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/hadzikadunic-stekao-pravo-nastupa-za-bih/1871644|title=Hadžikadunić stekao pravo nastupa za BiH|website=fokus.ba|date=16 September 2020|access-date=17 September 2020|language=bs}}</ref> Later that month, he received his first senior call up, for the [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying play-offs]] against [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] and [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League A#Group 1|2020–21 UEFA Nations League A]] games against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] and [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/309824-bajevic-objavio-spisak-pozvao-je-cetiri-nova-igraca|title=Bajević objavio spisak, pozvao je četiri nova igrača|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=28 September 2020|access-date=1 October 2020|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the Netherlands on 11 October.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/zmajevi-remizirali-protiv-mocne-nizozemske/67921|title=Zmajevi remizirali protiv moćne Nizozemske|website=faktor.ba|date=11 October 2020|access-date=13 October 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Hadžikadunić was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

